==Old High German==
===Etymology===
Common Germanic *''[[hultam]]'', from an Indo-European root ''*kldo-'', from ''*kel-'' "to cut". See also ''[[halb]]''.

Germanic cognates include Old English ''[[holt]]'', Old Norse ''[[holt]]''

